          'Cause I know

25:48.781 --> 25:50.781
        You run, you run,
       you run from me

25:50.783 --> 25:53.050
  Come on.
  It's time for the best part!

25:53.052 --> 25:55.119
- Whoo!
-  -Catch you later!

25:55.121 --> 25:58.589
   Uh, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

25:58.591 --> 26:00.291
            Come on!

26:00.293 --> 26:03.294
 What about sharks or jellyfish?

26:03.296 --> 26:05.229
      When's the last time
      you went swimming?

26:05.231 --> 26:07.598
          In the ocean?

26:07.600 --> 26:08.866
            As a kid.

26:08.868 --> 26:10.834
      The last time
      I was here, probably.

26:10.836 --> 26:12.002
  Well, then, it's about time.

26:12.004 --> 26:14.572
          It's nice as!

27:21.941 --> 27:25.109
    The air's different here.

27:25.111 --> 27:27.411
  I mean, it's, like, perfume.

27:27.413 --> 27:30.080
      It's a bit different
      from New York, huh?

27:30.082 --> 27:31.882
     Margot said you model.

27:31.884 --> 27:34.318
      Yeah, yeah.
      Teen fashion, mostly,

27:34.320 --> 27:36.153
   but Mom's been
   training me for editorial.

27:36.155 --> 27:38.355
  Training? How hard can it be?

27:38.357 --> 27:39.823
- Chicka.
-    -What?

27:39.825 --> 27:41.358
 You just lie around in clothes.

27:41.360 --> 27:45.229
     I do that all the time.
     I'm doing it right now.

27:45.231 --> 27:46.897
    Yeah, it's -- it's okay.

27:46.899 --> 27:48.399
A lot of people think it's easy.

27:48.401 --> 27:52.002
  It actually requires
  a surprising amount of work.

27:52.004 --> 27:54.204
       Sof must be
       very proud of you.

27:54.206 --> 27:56.206
          Yeah, well...

27:56.208 --> 27:57.841
         I might take
         a break from...

27:57.843 --> 28:00.277
     modeling soon, anyway.

28:00.279 --> 28:02.246
    Yeah, I don't blame you.

28:02.248 --> 28:04.782
   That video was pretty mean.

28:05.418 --> 28:06.850
            I mean...

28:06.852 --> 28:08.786
       It wasn't that bad.

28:11.757 --> 28:14.358
      Yeah, look, there are
      a lot of people

28:14.360 --> 28:17.394
     who work really hard
     to get the cover shoot.

28:17.396 --> 28:21.131
   If you make one mistake,
   even if it's a little one,

28:21.133 --> 28:23.133
   it's the end of the world.

28:23.135 --> 28:25.069
 You know, it seems like you're

28:25.071 --> 28:27.471
    the most important person
    in the room.

28:27.473 --> 28:30.007
  In actuality, you're nobody.

28:34.947 --> 28:38.816
      You can't be perfect
      all the time.

28:38.818 --> 28:40.784
      I know a thing or two
      about making mistakes

28:40.786 --> 28:42.386
in front of a critical audience.

28:42.388 --> 28:44.822
  Oh, yeah.
  Like that time you wiped out

28:44.824 --> 28:46.490
- in the Wahine's Women's Open.
-  -Chicka.

28:46.492 --> 28:49.359
   What? It was in the heats,
   not even the final,

28:49.361 --> 28:52.096
       and she just, like,
       completely ate it.

28:52.098 --> 28:55.132
      Thank you.
      I forgot about that.

28:55.134 --> 28:57.234
 I did wipe out more than once.

28:57.236 --> 28:58.435
Mm-hmm.

28:58.437 --> 29:00.003
But every time I made a mistake,

29:00.005 --> 29:01.405
     I learned something --

29:01.407 --> 29:05.242
  something about my technique
  or my attitude,

29:05.244 --> 29:07.244
          who to trust.

29:07.246 --> 29:08.746
            Exactly.

29:08.748 --> 29:10.814
       And who cares what
       those fancy pantses

29:10.816 --> 29:12.449
   in New York think, anyway?

29:14.754 --> 29:16.019
     I know it sounds silly,

29:16.021 --> 29:19.356
     but where I come from,

29:19.358 --> 29:22.392
    the fashion that we wear,
    it's -- it's just art.

29:22.394 --> 29:23.994
         It's pure art.

29:23.996 --> 29:26.330
       You should see what
       these designers do.

29:26.332 --> 29:30.100
   They don't just buy fabrics
   and follow a pattern.

29:30.102 --> 29:32.469
   I mean, they're architects.

29:32.471 --> 29:34.071
     They -- They research,

29:34.073 --> 29:36.940
   and they're always
   hunting down new materials

29:36.942 --> 29:42.279
 and seeking out ways to make it
 all come together, you know?

29:42.281 --> 29:45.349
   You sound very passionate.

29:45.351 --> 29:49.419
      Yeah, I mean, it's
      just my observations.

29:49.421 --> 29:52.422
 Here's an idea -- Why don't you
 two go for a surf tomorrow?

29:52.424 --> 29:55.292
 It's gonna be a beautiful day.

29:55.294 --> 29:57.561
       Sweet.
       Yeah, let's do it.

29:57.563 --> 29:59.429
          I can't surf.

29:59.431 --> 30:01.098
   Oh, well, that's all right.

30:01.100 --> 30:03.400
   Neither could I before
   I went out the first time.

30:10.910 --> 30:13.277
               Up.

30:16.248 --> 30:18.816
      Upright. Okay.
      Move this back foot.

30:18.818 --> 30:20.484
Breathe in.

30:20.486 --> 30:23.187
 Feel the movement of the water.

30:23.189 --> 30:25.088
   You are a part of the sea.

30:25.090 --> 30:26.824
      You are the current.

30:26.826 --> 30:29.193
      You are a jellyfish.

30:29.195 --> 30:32.229
 You are at one with the ocean.
 You're a dolphin.

30:32.231 --> 30:33.831
 I don't think this is working.

30:33.833 --> 30:36.333
      Oh, well, this is
      how Margot taught me.

30:36.335 --> 30:37.935
    Yeah, speaking of Margot,

30:37.937 --> 30:39.403
     maybe she can come out
     with us next time.

30:39.405 --> 30:42.272
        Open your eyes!
        And go, Cora! Go!

30:42.274 --> 30:44.908
         Paddle! Paddle!

30:47.279 --> 30:50.614
--Yeah, girl!

30:55.321 --> 30:59.623
         Whoo! Go, Cora!

31:14.240 --> 31:17.608
- Hello?
  -Margot.

31:17.610 --> 31:19.977
              Sof.

31:19.979 --> 31:22.880
      Hey, uh, how are you?

31:22.882 --> 31:24.514
              Fine.

31:24.516 --> 31:27.351
 Well, as fine as you can be
 when your daughter skips town.

31:27.353 --> 31:29.119
     Oh, I thought as much.

31:29.121 --> 31:32.055
  Didn't seem like you to push
  for a last-minute holiday.

31:34.393 --> 31:36.460
      I haven't heard
      from you in a while.

31:36.462 --> 31:38.362
I have tried to call.

31:40.900 --> 31:42.199
     Did you get the flowers
     I sent for --

31:42.201 --> 31:43.967
Yeah. Yeah, I did.

31:43.969 --> 31:46.937
             Thanks.

31:48.007 --> 31:51.308
     I meant to call back,
     but, well, you know...

31:52.311 --> 31:55.412
        So, Cora grew up.

31:55.414 --> 31:57.014
        She's great, Sof.

31:57.016 --> 31:58.582
    She's -- She's gorgeous.

31:58.584 --> 32:02.319
        Yeah, she is.
        Is she all right?

32:02.321 --> 32:04.021
    Not getting in your way?

32:04.023 --> 32:06.123
   No, no, no, no. Not at all.

32:06.125 --> 32:07.524
       I mean, she was --

32:07.526 --> 32:09.359
   she was a bit out of sorts
   when she arrived,

32:09.361 --> 32:11.395
  but actually,
  she's out surfing right now.

