  and now I'm giving it to you.

36:16.708 --> 36:19.743
           -Ohh! Ohh!
           -Careful.

36:19.745 --> 36:21.778
        Have fun with it.

36:21.780 --> 36:24.214
            Go wild.
            -Yeah.

36:24.216 --> 36:27.717
   No one's ever really asked
   for my opinion before.

36:27.719 --> 36:30.220
         More fool them.

36:30.222 --> 36:31.421
         Do you got it?
         -Yeah.

36:31.423 --> 36:33.390
         -Shall I help?
         -No. Arm day.

36:33.392 --> 36:34.958
  All right, I'll stand behind
  you in case you drop it.

37:22.674 --> 37:25.642
        Ah, she's flying.

37:25.644 --> 37:27.744
         It's beautiful.

37:27.746 --> 37:29.713
       It's like a dance.

37:29.715 --> 37:31.648
It's 'cause
 they're working together --

37:31.650 --> 37:33.450
       surfer and the sea.

37:33.452 --> 37:36.419
  Can't tell with the wave ends
  and she begins.

37:43.695 --> 37:46.563
 First thing -- We're gonna need
 some awesome surfer girls.

37:46.565 --> 37:47.864
   Can you help me with that?

37:47.866 --> 37:50.033
      Yeah. You're looking
      at one, sister.

37:50.035 --> 37:52.836
            Second...

37:52.838 --> 37:55.939
     Can you keep a secret?

37:55.941 --> 37:57.574
             Sealed.

38:02.514 --> 38:05.582
  Yes, I'll come back to you

38:05.584 --> 38:10.654
         No, I won't ask
        where you run

38:10.656 --> 38:14.357
         Under the sun

38:14.359 --> 38:18.361
  Yes, I'll come back to you

38:18.363 --> 38:23.066
      Then I'll ask,
     "What have we done?"

38:23.068 --> 38:25.535
         Under the sun

39:04.543 --> 39:07.644
     To be free, be awake

39:07.646 --> 39:12.515
       Big breath
      that you can't fake

39:12.517 --> 39:16.519
       Once you've begun

39:16.521 --> 39:19.889
    On the right side,
   coming on the right time

39:19.891 --> 39:22.926
    On the right time,
   coming on the right side

39:22.928 --> 39:25.962
    On the right side,
   coming on the right time

39:25.964 --> 39:29.499
    On the right time,
   coming on the right side

40:19.151 --> 40:22.452
  Thought this might get
  the creative juices flowing.

40:45.877 --> 40:47.944
     These are really good.

40:47.946 --> 40:49.512
           Thank you.

40:49.514 --> 40:51.548
       Do you see them
       in your head first

40:51.550 --> 40:54.050
     and then draw it,
     or does it just happen?

40:54.052 --> 40:56.052
     Yeah, yeah,
     I see them in my head.

40:56.054 --> 40:59.656
 Well -- Or I feel it, actually.

40:59.658 --> 41:01.891
            -Feel it?
            -Yeah.

41:01.893 --> 41:05.161
  I imagine what it would feel
  like if I was wearing it.

41:07.732 --> 41:10.099
- Hello?

41:10.101 --> 41:13.169
       Whoa! And goodbye.

41:13.171 --> 41:15.705
          Chicka, wait.

41:15.707 --> 41:16.840
           Come here.

41:18.944 --> 41:21.144
   I need you to be my model.

41:21.146 --> 41:22.512
              What?

41:22.514 --> 41:24.147
         Little, old me?

41:24.149 --> 41:27.116
I thought you'd never ask.

41:29.921 --> 41:32.655
         It's, uh, nice.

41:32.657 --> 41:34.624
      It's not exactly
      what I was going for.

41:34.626 --> 41:37.227
    Hmm...
    Maybe if I strike a pose.

41:37.229 --> 41:39.963
Ohh! Sorry!

41:39.965 --> 41:43.066
     We need functionality,
     not just aesthetics.

41:43.068 --> 41:45.702
 I could skate down the runway.

41:45.704 --> 41:47.036
Whoo!

41:47.038 --> 41:49.772
              -No!
              -Aah!

43:25.604 --> 43:26.736
Need a hand?

43:26.738 --> 43:29.072
               No.

43:29.074 --> 43:31.007
           Thank you.

43:33.812 --> 43:36.012
        We have a, uh --

43:36.014 --> 43:38.081
   a certain percentage of --

43:38.083 --> 43:42.952
     of customers that will
     only seem to book once.

43:42.954 --> 43:43.987
      Is that a statement,

43:43.989 --> 43:46.356
   or do you want my opinion?

43:46.358 --> 43:47.857
   Well, you've never been one

43:47.859 --> 43:49.692
      to keep your opinion
      to yourself.

43:52.030 --> 43:55.231
       Well, in that case,

43:55.233 --> 43:57.300
      maybe you should stop
      running your lessons

43:57.302 --> 44:01.170
  like a military exercise
  and let people have some fun.

44:01.172 --> 44:04.140
 That's all fun and games until
 someone runs out of business.

44:09.147 --> 44:10.780
          What is this?
          What is it?

44:10.782 --> 44:12.382
 This music --
 I'm nearly falling asleep here.

44:12.384 --> 44:13.883
         It's the blues.

44:13.885 --> 44:16.853
    Yeah, I'll say. Shocking.

44:16.855 --> 44:18.121
         Oh, here we go.

44:18.123 --> 44:20.790
     You're gonna like this.

44:23.995 --> 44:26.095
         That's better.

44:26.097 --> 44:27.764
         We never have,

44:27.766 --> 44:29.432
        and we never will
        agree on music.

44:29.434 --> 44:32.235
            Mm-hmm.
            Come on.

44:32.237 --> 44:33.403
     No. The '90s are over.

44:33.405 --> 44:35.104
 You need to let them go, Owen.

44:35.106 --> 44:36.939
            Come on.

45:15.480 --> 45:19.449
    We had some good times --
    you, me, and Caleb.

45:19.451 --> 45:20.850
              Yeah.

45:20.852 --> 45:23.720
     We were pretty blessed.

45:23.722 --> 45:27.457
  Sometimes I feel like he's --

45:27.459 --> 45:30.193
 I feel like he's slipping away.

45:30.195 --> 45:33.730
  He's still out there, Margs.

45:33.732 --> 45:36.099
      I feel him every time
      I paddle out.

46:17.242 --> 46:18.808
    Hold your horses, kiddo.

46:18.810 --> 46:20.810
     Oh, hey. Just gonna
     go catch up to Margot.

46:20.812 --> 46:23.379
        Why don't you put
        these on instead?

46:23.381 --> 46:25.081
   We-- I would, but she's --

46:25.083 --> 46:28.151
       Margot isn't gonna
       go for a surf.

46:28.153 --> 46:30.052
    Uh, she just walked down.
    I just saw her.

46:30.054 --> 46:33.890
      Well, that's true,
      but she won't go out.

46:33.892 --> 46:35.558
What's she doing, then?

46:35.560 --> 46:38.995
The same thing she's done
 every day for the last year.

46:38.997 --> 46:41.998
      She doesn't go
      in the water anymore.

46:42.000 --> 46:45.535
     Wait, she -- she hasn't
     surfed in a year?

46:45.537 --> 46:47.570
  I thought she was
  a pro surfer -- the trophies.

46:47.572 --> 46:49.539
     Well, she is, darling.

46:49.541 --> 46:52.141
That -- That doesn't make sense.

46:52.143 --> 46:53.976
Sometimes
  when we're hurting,

46:53.978 --> 46:55.211
  the last thing we want to do

46:55.213 --> 46:58.281
      is what will make us
      feel better.

46:58.283 --> 47:03.186
    Is she scared because of
    what happened to Caleb?

47:03.188 --> 47:05.087
        When I was a kid,
        we had this big,

47:05.089 --> 47:06.556
       old eucalyptus tree
       in the garden.

47:06.558 --> 47:08.891
  It was beautiful.
  It had a little magpie in it,

47:08.893 --> 47:11.194
      and every morning,
      it would warble away.

47:11.196 --> 47:12.862
      For five years,
      I was sent to school

47:12.864 --> 47:15.565
      to the sound of that
      happy, little fellow.

47:15.567 --> 47:18.401
  One day, my father got an ax,

47:18.403 --> 47:20.069
  and he chopped the tree down.

47:20.071 --> 47:21.437
        I was devastated.

47:21.439 --> 47:23.906
    No more branches to cast
    shadows on the wall.

47:23.908 --> 47:26.375
       No more Mr. Magpie.

47:26.377 --> 47:27.944
        We got a pool --

47:27.946 --> 47:29.478
  an above-ground monstrosity.

47:29.480 --> 47:32.949
   Well, it was so hot
   the pavements were melting,

47:32.951 --> 47:35.451
       and I still refused
       to get in it.

47:35.453 --> 47:36.919
   Why did you hate the pool?

47:36.921 --> 47:38.487
 Because if I'd got in the pool,

47:38.489 --> 47:41.290
   it would be like I was okay
   with the tree being gone,

47:41.292 --> 47:44.126
       and I wasn't.
       I was still angry.

47:44.128 --> 47:46.095
    But I realized there were
    things to be happy about,

47:46.097 --> 47:49.532
    and that put the sad
    things into perspective.

47:49.534 --> 47:51.300
Things happen and they change us

47:51.302 --> 47:54.270
   and we can't control that.

47:54.272 --> 47:57.907
     What you can control
     is how they change you.

47:59.544 --> 48:01.944
     I'm sorry about Caleb.

48:01.946 --> 48:03.145
      And about your tree.

48:03.147 --> 48:05.181
Oh, don't be.

48:05.183 --> 48:07.650
    Now, 4:00 p.m. tomorrow,
    Chicka says

48:07.652 --> 48:10.353
    she's lined up some girls
    for the fitting.

48:10.355 --> 48:12.488
         Oh, yeah. Uh...

48:12.490 --> 48:15.291
         You'll be fine.
         Walk this way.

48:15.293 --> 48:17.994
      Now -- Now, come over
      here to me,

48:17.996 --> 48:19.629
     and you see up here?
     That's what I'm doing.

48:19.631 --> 48:21.230
     You just nip those off.

48:31.376 --> 48:35.478
- Cora! Whoo!

48:35.480 --> 48:37.113
              -Hey.
              -Hey!

48:37.115 --> 48:39.949
             Yeah!
             -Okay.

48:39.951 --> 48:42.618
Ooh, check it out, girls.

48:44.255 --> 48:46.555
        I thought we were
        getting bikinis.

48:46.557 --> 48:49.692
    No, uh, bikinis weren't
    invented until the '40s.

48:49.694 --> 48:52.395
     Your outfit is inspired
     by the Edwardian Era.

49:06.277 --> 49:07.576
             Ta-da!

49:07.578 --> 49:09.312
       What are you doing?

49:09.314 --> 49:12.048
It's heaps better.
 Now you can see my legs.

49:12.050 --> 49:14.617
 Oh, is it? Is it heaps better?

49:14.619 --> 49:17.353
Well, is there anything else
you'd like to make heaps better?

49:17.355 --> 49:18.688
          No. What? No.

49:18.690 --> 49:20.323
     I didn't realize
     Tea Tree Beach was home

49:20.325 --> 49:22.058
    to such a fashion expert.

49:22.060 --> 49:23.592
   Uh, I just thought that --

49:23.594 --> 49:26.028
   Why don't you take over
   and design the whole thing?

49:26.030 --> 49:28.698
  Come on, Cora.
  She didn't mean to upset you.

49:28.700 --> 49:30.633
       Dressing up is
       supposed to be fun.

49:30.635 --> 49:32.635
        You think this is
        just dress-up?

49:36.074 --> 49:37.373
       What's her problem?

49:39.143 --> 49:40.443
               Ah!

49:40.445 --> 49:42.611
    What's going on in there?

49:42.613 --> 49:44.580
      She ruined my design.

49:44.582 --> 49:47.149
     And talking to her like
     that's gonna fix it?

49:47.151 --> 49:48.985
    She hacked it to pieces.

49:48.987 --> 49:51.187
     Well, I don't know.
     Does she have a point?

49:51.189 --> 49:52.989
      A point?
      It's like you people

49:52.991 --> 49:55.324
     don't know anything
     about beauty or design.

49:55.326 --> 49:57.259
          "You people."

49:57.261 --> 49:58.561
     It's these people
     that have embraced you

49:58.563 --> 50:01.364
    and asked you to help out
    with their festival.

50:01.366 --> 50:03.232
      What have your people
      done for you, Cora?

50:03.234 --> 50:06.402
    Pushed you around,
    spread rumors about you?

50:06.404 --> 50:10.239
  You're right. My people
  are nothing like your people.

50:10.241 --> 50:12.708
     And I'm fine with that.

50:27.158 --> 50:29.625
Thanks,
  but I'm not hungry.

50:29.627 --> 50:33.396
      Well, I'll just leave
      it here, then.

50:33.398 --> 50:37.066
      Aunt Margot, did you
      and Caleb ever fight?

50:40.705 --> 50:42.772
             Never.

50:42.774 --> 50:45.441
Yes.

50:45.443 --> 50:47.410
        Oh, all the time.

50:47.412 --> 50:51.280
   Blue Soul nearly killed us
   more than once.

50:51.282 --> 50:54.550
        Why do you keep
        running it, then?

50:54.552 --> 50:57.787
  It's all I have left of him.

50:57.789 --> 51:00.389
   Is that why you hate Owen?

51:00.391 --> 51:03.526
       I don't hate Owen.

51:03.528 --> 51:05.561
       The three of us
       were great friends.

51:07.532 --> 51:10.699
Owen was there surfing
with Caleb the day that he died.

51:15.506 --> 51:17.106
       I heard the fitting
       didn't go so well.

51:17.108 --> 51:19.341
           Ugh! Yeah.

51:19.343 --> 51:21.744
       I kind of lost it.
       -You're passionate.

51:21.746 --> 51:23.446
    Don't apologize for that.

51:23.448 --> 51:26.782
You just need a bit of patience.

51:29.554 --> 51:31.387
          I don't know.

51:31.389 --> 51:34.590
  I-I constantly just feel like
  I'm saying the wrong thing.

51:34.592 --> 51:38.294
       It takes courage
       to speak your mind.

51:38.296 --> 51:41.697
 Our family makes strong women,
 and you're one of them.

51:41.699 --> 51:44.533
        Be proud of that.

51:46.104 --> 51:47.236
          That chicken.

51:47.238 --> 51:48.804
          Belinda! No!

51:48.806 --> 51:51.507
       Out, out, out,
       or I will cook you!

52:11.696 --> 52:14.630
Chicka. Hey.

52:14.632 --> 52:17.700
      I owe you an apology.

52:17.702 --> 52:19.735
   I'm sorry about yesterday.

52:19.737 --> 52:21.470
You were real mad.

52:21.472 --> 52:24.640
   I thought you might explode
   into a thousand pieces.

52:24.642 --> 52:26.242
             I know.

52:26.244 --> 52:28.911
     Do you think the others
     might forgive me?

52:28.913 --> 52:31.313
  We're going out to surf soon
  if you want to join.

52:31.315 --> 52:33.516
       Yeah, I'd love to.

52:33.518 --> 52:34.917
You looking for Tom?

52:34.919 --> 52:36.785
       He's on the beach.
       And don't worry.

52:36.787 --> 52:39.255
      He's not one to
      bear grudges, either.

52:41.359 --> 52:43.292
              Here.

52:45.329 --> 52:46.662
           Thank you.

53:00.912 --> 53:02.411
              Hey.

53:02.413 --> 53:04.513
Hey.

53:06.584 --> 53:08.951
      They won't hurt you.

53:11.589 --> 53:14.223
              Whoo.

53:14.225 --> 53:17.693
       They're beautiful.
       Whose are they?

53:17.695 --> 53:20.329
           Don't know.

53:23.401 --> 53:25.601
  Hey, listen, I was thinking,

53:25.603 --> 53:29.471
  and I might bring out
  a line of bikinis, after all.

53:29.473 --> 53:30.906
         That's a shame.

53:30.908 --> 53:32.608
      Kind of liked
      the knee-length look.

54:54.825 --> 54:56.592
             Hello?

55:29.694 --> 55:31.427
Hey.

55:31.429 --> 55:32.561
Hey.

55:32.563 --> 55:34.430
    This place is incredible.

55:34.432 --> 55:38.033
    These boards are amazing.

55:38.035 --> 55:40.636
     Margot really wouldn't
     like you being in here.

55:40.638 --> 55:42.938
This is so beautiful.

55:42.940 --> 55:47.776
   I almost thought
   it would have a heartbeat.

55:47.778 --> 55:49.712
It's not finished.

55:49.714 --> 55:52.348
        I need to, um...

55:52.350 --> 55:53.849
    It needs to be finished.

55:53.851 --> 55:55.918
   Wait, is this place yours?

55:55.920 --> 55:58.821
   This was Caleb's workshop.

55:58.823 --> 56:01.357
      Those are his boards.

56:01.359 --> 56:03.492
        This one is mine.

56:05.129 --> 56:08.130
    Wait, you design boards?

56:08.132 --> 56:10.599
        You never asked.

56:12.737 --> 56:15.604
    So, how come you haven't
    finished it, then?

56:17.007 --> 56:19.675
    Can we come out of here?

56:21.812 --> 56:24.480
              Yeah.

56:35.793 --> 56:37.693
     Nice to have you home.

56:37.695 --> 56:39.762
             Mm-hmm.

56:39.764 --> 56:42.464
      It's good to be back.

56:42.466 --> 56:44.633
          Are you sure?

56:44.635 --> 56:47.703
       Sometimes I think
       you prefer touring.

56:48.973 --> 56:51.840
         Are you fishing
         for something?

56:54.011 --> 56:56.478
        I'm proud of you.

56:56.480 --> 56:58.714
     Those waves in Indo --
     They were big.

56:58.716 --> 57:00.182
               Mm.

57:00.184 --> 57:03.852
       And to be honest...

57:03.854 --> 57:06.688
 I was really worried about you.

57:06.690 --> 57:07.890
   You know if it's up to me,

57:07.892 --> 57:11.693
    I will always come home.

57:11.695 --> 57:13.862
            My wife,

57:13.864 --> 57:17.633
    out taming monster waves.

57:29.180 --> 57:31.580
           I love you.

57:54.238 --> 57:56.738
          Ow! Belinda!

57:58.008 --> 57:59.942
           No, no, no.

58:13.824 --> 58:16.058
  Oh, no,
  you're not doing that today.

58:16.060 --> 58:17.726
    Chicka, I really want to.

58:17.728 --> 58:19.495
  Oh, but the surf's too good!

58:19.497 --> 58:21.897
       And everyone's out.

58:21.899 --> 58:23.866
Even some by the name of Thomas.

58:26.504 --> 58:28.904
             Hmm...

58:28.906 --> 58:31.173
Well, we better get going, then.

58:31.175 --> 58:32.908
Let's go.

59:36.807 --> 59:39.875
   Um, this is very isolated.

59:39.877 --> 59:41.243
      Should I be worried?

59:41.245 --> 59:44.646
      No. It is a bit weird
      around here, though.

59:44.648 --> 59:47.349
  When I was a kid, I thought
  a witch lived in these rocks.

59:47.351 --> 59:49.785
      My brothers told me
      stories about her --

59:49.787 --> 59:51.720
     how she drowned sailors

59:51.722 --> 59:55.857
    and rode whales
    to the bottom of the sea.

59:55.859 --> 59:57.826
  Have you told me that before?

59:57.828 --> 01:00:00.095
         Don't think so.

01:00:04.702 --> 01:00:06.001
         It's cool, huh?

01:00:08.005 --> 01:00:10.272
Cora Hamilton!

01:00:12.910 --> 01:00:16.011
       So, you still want
       to make boards?

01:00:16.013 --> 01:00:19.615
    Sort of forgotten
    about them, to be honest.

01:00:19.617 --> 01:00:23.151
 I haven't been in the workshop
 for about a year.

01:00:23.153 --> 01:00:24.720
         Do you miss it?

01:00:24.722 --> 01:00:28.023
        Yeah. Yeah, I do.

01:00:28.025 --> 01:00:31.126
 I love starting with nothing
 and seeing it sort of reveal --

01:00:31.128 --> 01:00:34.162
      Reveal itself to you.

01:00:34.164 --> 01:00:38.033
      Yeah. Yeah. Exactly.

01:00:39.203 --> 01:00:41.269
          I don't know.

01:00:41.271 --> 01:00:43.772
      It kind of seemed
      like he was in there

01:00:43.774 --> 01:00:45.841
     waiting to be finished.

01:00:45.843 --> 01:00:48.043
     -Who?
     -Your unfinished board.

01:00:48.045 --> 01:00:49.778
 It's like he was just in there,

01:00:49.780 --> 01:00:52.180
  waiting for you to come back
  in and finish him up.

01:00:52.182 --> 01:00:53.348
       It's a "he," is he?

01:00:53.350 --> 01:00:55.417
           Well, yeah.

01:00:55.419 --> 01:00:57.686
     Well, a woman wouldn't
     wait around like that.

01:01:01.992 --> 01:01:05.193
          You did that.

01:01:05.195 --> 01:01:06.762
              What?

01:01:06.764 --> 01:01:10.065
   You don't remember, do you?

01:01:10.067 --> 01:01:12.067
       Wait, that was you?

01:01:12.069 --> 01:01:13.702
   You were that annoying boy

01:01:13.704 --> 01:01:15.203
  that I used to chase around?

01:01:15.205 --> 01:01:18.206
              Yes!

01:01:18.208 --> 01:01:20.008
  -So I have been here before.
  -Mm-hmm.

01:01:20.010 --> 01:01:21.977
       And you've told me
       that story before.

01:01:21.979 --> 01:01:24.212
      You tried to scare me
      with the witch.

01:01:24.214 --> 01:01:25.947
 Bet you can't catch me anymore.

01:01:29.053 --> 01:01:31.753
Okay.

01:01:36.060 --> 01:01:37.392
              Huh.

01:01:37.394 --> 01:01:39.728
 So a guy can wait around, then.

01:01:39.730 --> 01:01:42.397
      I wasn't waiting for
      you to come back,

01:01:42.399 --> 01:01:44.466
      but I'm glad you did.

01:02:11.929 --> 01:02:14.262
   Hello, you've reached 1955.

01:02:14.264 --> 01:02:17.733
      There's no Internet
